OL,3,CKing appoints composer and engineer as
OL,4,COrder of the Thistle members
OL,6,FTwo Scots have been appointed as
OL,7,Fmembers of the Order of the Thistle by
OL,8,Fthe King.
OL,10,FProfessor Sir Jim McDonald and Sir
OL,11,FJames MacMillan were both appointed by
OL,12,FCharles to what is widely regarded as
OL,13,Fthe highest honour in Scotland for
OL,14,Ftheir notable contributions to
OL,15,Fengineering and music respectively.
OL,17,FThe King is the sovereign of the order
OL,18,Fand appoints whom he deems fit
OL,19,Fentirely through his own accord,
OL,20,Fwithout advice from third parties such
OL,21,Fas the Government.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
